                            <comment id="133080" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 28 Oct 2016 15:20:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I recall requests for additional variants of PUT, POST, and DELETE. It makes sense to have the basic variants for PATCH to be on par with the other HTTP methods. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="133409" author="arjen.poutsma" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2016 09:55:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/commit/dbe81bef52e1bcaf802663d2bb3236c69f922512&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/commit/dbe81bef52e1bcaf802663d2bb3236c69f922512&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="133883" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 3 Dec 2016 20:42:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we got a second request for this already (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-14974&quot; title=&quot;Introduce patchForObject/patchForLocation to RestTemplate/RestOperations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-14974&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-14974&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and this seems like a straightforward enough addition, I&apos;ll consider it for a backport to 4.3.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="133901" author="edeandrea" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2016 12:57:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A backport to 4.x would be great!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
